Real Madrid have released a strong squad to face Sevilla in today’s La Liga fixture at the Santiago Bernabéu. Real Madrid manager, Zinedine Zidane named a 19-man squad to tackle the visitors in a post on the club’s official website on Friday. Zidane’s men head to the game after defeating Atletico Madrid to win this season’s Spanish Super Cup last weekend. REAL MADRID SQUAD: Goalkeepers: Courtois, Areola and Altube. Defenders: Carvajal, Militão, Varane, Nacho, Marcelo and Mendy. Midfielders: Kroos, Modric, Casemiro and Isco. Forwards: Benzema, Lucas Vázquez, Jović, Brahim, Vinicius Jr. and Rodrygo. The kick-off time for the match is 4pm.